com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.datastore.id

Interface ISnomedIdentifierService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSnomedIdentifierService, CisSnomedIdentifierService, DefaultSnomedIdentifierService

    public interface ISnomedIdentifierService
    The SNOMED CT identifier service interface generates and maintains identifiers according to the Technical Implementation Guide. IDs are generated by defining the ComponentCategory (the component type we need ID for), and an optional namespace parameter. The returned SNOMED CT ID will have a valid check-digit, partition-identifier, and the optional namespace identifier.
    Since:
    4.0
    See Also:
    www.snomed.org/tig?t=trg_app_sctid

      • generate

        Set<String> generate(String namespace,
                     ComponentCategory category,
                     int quantity)
        Generates multiple SNOMED CT IDs for the defined ComponentCategory with the defined extension namespace.
        Parameters:
        namespace - the extension namespace to use when generating the ID
        category - the component type to generate ID for
        quantity - the number of IDs to generate
        Returns:
        a collection of generated IDs (in Assigned state)
